(67395, 7063, 6127, 10, 'Bajan Honk (Steve Koven Trio)', '　Steve Koven在加拿大多倫多出生，7歲開始彈鋼琴。\r\n1987年，在約克大學靠「當代即興演奏」贏得了BFA學位，成為職業音樂家。\r\n　此外，Steve Koven的「鋼琴獨奏音樂會」於世界各地巡演，遍及北美洲，歐洲和加勒比。在沒有巡演或在錄音室時，Steve Koven為電視或電影作曲，並進行授課和研討會，專注於即興演奏的發展和音樂表達自我。\r\n　Steve Koven從2003年開始，在約克大學音樂學院教導「當代即興」與「爵士鋼琴」。2012年獲得紐約大學作曲碩士學位。成為一個教育工作者，Steve Koven已在中國，日本，哥倫比亞，巴巴多斯和墨西哥進行授課及研討會。專注於發展即興技能和音樂的自我表達。', '2013-10-21 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 15, '(純音樂)', '', 310, '', 'Steve Koven', 'N/A', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-10-22 12:40:30', '2015-03-12 14:02:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(67396, 7063, 6127, 11, 'Walk On (Lori Nuic)', '　在廣播和電視台黃金時段，你一定聽過她的聲音。Lori Nuic深情歌聲早已唱進每位觀眾心中。 \r\n　Lori Nuic寬廣的音樂品味與影響力，完全表現於她充滿爆發力的歌聲中。很難將Lori Nuic歸類，她就是有辦法讓大家持續想聽下去。一連串的現場演出更讓她建立一群死忠歌迷。\r\n　「2005年蜂蜜果醬季」的《最佳歌曲獎》(這是與Saukrates共同製作的歌曲)，同年底她更贏得《91.5未來最具天分》的獎項。「2006加拿大音樂週」的《尋找都市星全國冠軍》(加拿大知名女歌首納麗Furtado也穫得同樣獎項)。2008年夏天，Lori Nuic拿下「多倫多獨立音樂」的《最佳流行音樂》獎項。\r\n　Lori Nuic的首支單曲『Rear View』在「91.5 Beat電台」首週進榜從27名中位居第12名，沒有經過常規的宣傳，僅透過CHR和都市電台強力播歌，全國各地都可聽到她的聲音並獲得廣大的注意。單曲『Rear View』更於電台停留16週之久。 \r\n　在多倫多、蜂蜜果醬、CMW以及全國爵士樂獎項中的表現已為她建立口杯。不僅被邀請為知名Neve Campbell、David Mirvish及已故的Gregory Hines在節目中表演，與知名藝人歌手「就是紅色Raul Midon、大衛福特、Moka Only(Swollen的成員)、Keisha Chante、Jully Black與Shawn Desman.」拼盤演出。更為加拿大當紅電視選秀節目中，最後決賽選手Toya Alexis與Gary Beals合音，她的歌聲也出現在Toya與加拿大R& B歌手Carlos Morgan專輯中。\r\n　Lori Nuic在電視、電影和戲劇的幕後工作，幫助她的演出充滿爆發力。2008年夏天在多倫多製作『Little Shop of Horrors』之後，被邀請到聖地亞哥、智利等地做一次短期巡迴演出。2009年Lori Nuic在《加拿大音樂週(CMW)》的LIVE表演令人印象深刻，讓來自中國的代表團驚豔。\r\n　Lori Nuic的專輯【The Red Chronicles】很快將在亞洲市場發行。目前她為即將展開的亞洲巡迴演出，緊羅密鼓的在多倫多寫歌與準備演出。', '2013-10-21 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 15, '『Walk On』\r\n\r\nSeen you walking down the street the other day boy\r\nLike a dream, happens every day boy\r\nDo you see what I see every time our eyes meet\r\nI feel happiness in a heartbeat\r\n\r\nI guess this ain''t us\r\nWe could not paint trust\r\nWithout all the colours that are only gathered in time\r\nSo go if you must\r\nI guess we''re just strangers, strangers\r\n\r\nWalk on\r\nWalk on\r\nWalk on\r\n\r\n\r\nHere you come again towards me\r\nWondering who you might''ve seen before me\r\nCuz visions of you and me\r\nAnd all we could every be\r\nPass through my mind so quickly and then you''re gone\r\n\r\nI guess this ain''t us\r\nWe could not paint trust\r\nWithout all the colours that are only gathered in time\r\nSo go if you must\r\nI guess we''re just strangers, strangers\r\n\r\nWalk on\r\nWalk on\r\nWalk on\r\n\r\n\r\nEven if I had the chance, ooh I''d never say\r\nCould never face if you had to walk away\r\nSo I''ll just let you play and linger in my mind\r\nI figure it''s the only way to let my pride survive\r\n\r\nI guess this ain''t us\r\nWe could not paint trust\r\nWithout all the colours that are only gathered in time\r\nSo go if you must\r\nI guess we''re just strangers, strangers\r\n\r\nWalk on\r\nWalk on\r\nWalk on\r\n', '', 209, '', 'Karl Amani Wailoo + Colin D. Munroe + Lori Nuic + Nuki Tunes', 'Karl Amani Wailoo + Colin D. Munroe + Lori Nuic + Nuki Tunes', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-10-22 12:42:15', '2015-03-12 14:02:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(67397, 7063, 6127, 12, '7 Months (Sunshine State 陽光國度合唱團)', '【Sunshine State陽光國度合唱團】是由Aleza和James Bryan在一次偶然的合作組成。兩人的關係是病人與音樂治療師，當在境內首屈一指的吉他手兼製作人James用吉他為Aleza治療時，Aleza用歌聲述說自己的故事，一個獨自在都會中生活的女性，這樣的互動彷彿成為了一股相當正面的能量，因此，成就了屬於Sunshine State的音樂！！\r\n　Aleza首支單曲『Day Job』中用柔順清亮又簡潔有力的歌聲唱出上班族對生活的單調，壓力和徬徨想逃脫，卻又無可奈何的妥協，符合上班族的心聲，因此在加拿大被封為「上班族國歌」，隨著機車的電視廣告強力放送下，立刻在網路上引起網友強烈詢問，唱片公司順應市場需求在台灣推出專輯。專輯一堆出單曲【Day Job日赴一日】首週便榮登 KKBOX西洋單曲榜第一名。\r\n　【Sunshine State陽光國度合唱團】這個名字連同他們的同名專輯迅速在加拿大境內四處流傳，而Aleza的歌聲都能唱出內心世界搭配James在音樂上創造的鮮明層次。', '2013-10-21 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 15, '『7 Months』\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\n7 months\r\nI heard you say – baby\r\nAs you checked your messages this morning\r\nPack your bags leave it all for a country far away\r\nThe job that you’d been dreaming of was calling\r\n\r\nIt hasn’t been very long\r\nAt least according to my closest friends\r\nWatch your heart take it slow have some fun is all they  say\r\nBut I’m still spending all the time I can\r\nWith you\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\nfunny how \r\nthis twist of fate\r\ngoes to show that nothing’s ever perfect\r\nhad to kiss a lot of frogs ‘till you finally came along\r\nbut now we don’t have a lot of time to work with\r\n\r\nyou’ll be away for so long\r\nalready writing letters in my head\r\nso we walk and we laugh like we’ll always be together\r\nas we take one step closer to the edge\r\nbut we still pretend\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n', '', 231, '', 'A.Coldevin + J.Bryan McCollum', 'A.Coldevin + J.Bryan McCollum', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-10-22 12:44:31', '2015-03-12 14:02:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(67398, 7063, 6127, 13, 'Someone Is You (Westpoint)', '　Westpoint是由5位傑出音樂人組合而成，Westpoint與多倫多重量級的製作人Joel Kazmi在2007年共同完成首張專輯【Goodbye Rocket】。並於同年獲得「多倫多獨立音樂獎」的《最佳搖滾獎》與《另類樂團獎》。 \r\n　2008年在加拿大展開一些巡演宣傳【Goodbye Rocket】專輯。Westpoint令人振奮的音樂、熱情的嗓音和有感染力的創作，肯定在聽過一次後，就會跟著唱。', '2013-10-21 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 15, '『Someone Is You』\r\n\r\nI''ve been looking for something\r\nSomewhere out there\r\nI''ve been looking for answers\r\nBut they''re nowhere\r\nI''ve been looking for someone\r\nAnd they don''t care\r\n\r\nI see you when\r\nI open up\r\nI know you''re there\r\nBut It''s not enough\r\nI''m looking for someone\r\nAnd someone is you\r\n\r\nI''ve been walking on backwards\r\nAnd forwards to see\r\nIf I could find someone \r\nSo perfect for me\r\nI knew when I found then\r\nThat someone is you\r\n\r\nI see you when\r\nI open up\r\nI know you''re there\r\nBut It''s not enough\r\n\r\nI see you when\r\nI open up\r\nI know you''re there\r\nBut It''s not enough\r\nI''m looking for someone\r\nAnd someone is you\r\n\r\nIsn''t anybody looking for the same damn thing\r\nWouldn''t anybody weathered have a reason to sing\r\nLet it out. Let it out. Let it out.\r\n\r\nI''ve been looking for something\r\nI''ve been looking for answers\r\nBut they''re nowhere\r\nI''ve been looking for someone\r\nBut they don''t care\r\n\r\nI see you when \r\nI open up\r\nI know you''re there\r\nBut it''s not enough\r\nOh I''m still looking for someone\r\nAnd someone is you\r\n', '', 225, '', 'Stephen Andrews + Taras Blyznik + Mordechai Harroch + Joel Kazmi + Jeffrey William + Kenny+Brandon R', 'Stephen Andrews + Taras Blyznik + Mordechai Harroch + Joel Kazmi + Jeffrey William + Kenny+Brandon R', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-10-22 12:46:35', '2015-03-12 14:02:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(67399, 7063, 6127, 14, 'Drinking Coffee (Renée Yoxon)', '　Renée Yoxon專注於爵士歌唱藝術。\r\n　2005年多倫多著名爵士歌手Tena Palmer啟發她開始學習爵士樂。\r\n　2010年，發行首張專輯【Let''s Call it a Day】，淒美歌曲搭配她豐富情感的演唱，讓專輯在發行一年內便很快銷售一空。\r\n　2011年，Renée Yoxon被認定為新興歌手，由國家藝術中心和Astral Radio提供資金，到紐約花了一個夏天與John McNeil、Janet Lawson、Peter Eldridge、Karen Nimereala共同學習。\r\n　2012年，Renée Yoxon發行第二張專輯，依然由她和鋼琴家Mark Ferguson共同製作。', '2013-10-21 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 15, '『Drinking Coffee』\r\n\r\nThe coffee at the bottom of my cup is cold and bitter\r\nBut I choke it down and hope the hurt gets swallowed on the way.\r\nI keep the cup pressed to my lips even though it''s empty\r\nAnd I hold it very still until the trembling goes away.\r\n\r\nBut I don''t know why I try to hide these feelings,\r\nAnd I don''t why I try to hide this pain\r\n‘Cause even though you''re right across the table from me, darling,\r\nI could wail and I could shout,\r\nI could let myself cry out,\r\nYou''d go on drinking coffee and never ask me to explain,\r\nOh you''d go on drinking coffee and never ask me to explain.\r\n\r\nI often think of packing up a bag and walking out\r\nAnd never turning back to see if you put up a fight\r\nBut our baby boys they have your eyes and how could mama tell them,\r\n“Your daddy never tread me wrong, but he never treat me right.”\r\n\r\nSo I go on trying to hide all these feelings\r\nAnd I go on trying to hide all this pain\r\nBut even though you''re right across the table from me, darling,\r\nI could wail and I could shout,\r\nI could let myself cry out,\r\nYou''d go on drinking coffee and never ask me to explain.\r\n\r\nSo I go on trying to hide all these feelings\r\nAnd I go on trying to hide all this pain\r\nBut even though you''re right across the table from me, darling,\r\nI could wail and I could shout,\r\nI could let myself cry out,\r\nYou''d go on drinking coffee and never ask me to explain,\r\nOh you''d go on drinking coffee and never ask me to explain,\r\nOh you''d go on drinking coffee and never ask me to explain.\r\n', '', 269, '', 'Renée Yoxon', 'Renée Yoxon', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-10-22 12:48:46', '2015-03-12 14:02:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
